'''sushi''' (''Collective Noun'')
# A Japanese dish consisting of rice, wrapped in seaweed, with a filling in the middle of the rice (which may vary from avocado to fish, or combinations), the ingredients are made into rolls which are cut into short cylinders. Otherwise called Californian rolls. This word is sometimes mistaken to have the meaning of [[sashimi]].